<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-302-678  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 302 678.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>MIS Week  March 26 1990 v11 n13 p34(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Retina scanners: eye-secure identification; a host of biometricdevices is bringing the future to users now.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Kanner, Nathaniel.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Retina scanners and other similar biometric devices that have longbeen the sole province of science fiction are becoming available,presenting users with some practical applications for high-techsecurity systems.andP;  Biometric devices use fingerprint, voiceprintor retina scanners to determine the identity of those accessing acomputer or secured area.andP;  Retina scanners bounce an infrared beamoff the person's retina, tracing the unique pattern of distinctblood vessels; the intensity of the reflection at different pointsis translated into numbers between 0 and 4,095, which are thenconverted into an 80-byte computer code forming an eye signature.andO;The small amount of data required gives retina scanning anadvantage over other biometric techniques; identifications can bemade in less than three seconds.andP;  Eyedentify Inc's Ibex retinascanning system is described.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     BiometricsSecurity SystemsHigh TechnologyProduct DevelopmentNew TechniqueEyeScanningUser IdentificationAccess Controls.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>